    "summary": "Sujata is the Group General Counsel for Expereo. She is a highly experienced senior legal professional with  experience of working with global organisations managing legal and enterprise risks, corporate governance, data protection, employment and regulatory issues. Prior to working in-house, Sujata had significant private practice experience with focus on corporate and M&A deals at Tier-1 international law firms such as White & Case LLP, Stephenson Harwood and leading Asian firm Rajah & Tann.\n\nSujata has a multi-cultural background, having worked and lived in Indonesia, Singapore, India, Hong Kong and the Netherlands and supported teams across US, LATAM, EMEA and APAC. She is trilingual in English, Hindi and Bahasa Indonesia. \n\nKey skills and strengths:\n-\tStrong M&A background with expertise in optimum deal structuring and having been involved in large and high-profile M&A, joint venture and capital market deals involving names such as Lehman Brothers, Rajawali Group, PT. Bumi Resources and Lokmat.\n-\tDeep knowledge of legal risks across the life cycle of a product from manufacturing to sale, including supply chain management, route-to-market, regulatory, labour, licensing, IP issues and crisis management.\n-\tProven project management skills evidenced by managing business expansion projects of USGBoral manufacturing plants in India, Vietnam and Thailand.\n-\tValued business partner collaborating well with business teams in APAC, US, EMEA ensuring business continuity within a compliant legal framework across finance, tax, IT and HR.\n-\tEfficient project management skills in managing external counsel based around the world.\n-\tExpert in managing compliance profiles of companies globally. Initiated compliance programs for companies on anti-bribery, international trade sanctions, data protection, code of conduct etc. and trained large groups of over 3000+ employees. Fascinated by the leap in legal tech Sujata has pioneered several risk management digital solutions for her organisation.\n\nSujata is passionate about ensuring businesses succeed in an ethical, compliant and sustainable manner and has used her legal skills to this end. Sujata is also a strong proponent of sustainability and leading organisations towards its ESG goals, particularly focusing on business ethics and D&I. She is also a member of the Women\u2019s Committee and Pro-bono Committee of the ACC, Singapore Chapter.",
